[
  "Hiroshi Mikitani is founder and CEO of Rakuten, Japan's biggest e-commerce retailer.",
  "In 2019, Rakuten posted a loss of $301 million, its first since 2011.",
  "The firm delayed the rollout of its new $5.5 billion mobile service, which was to start in October 2019, launching it in April 2020.",
  "In 2015, Rakuten invested $300 million in ride-sharing firm Lyft, an Uber competitor, and Mikitani joined Lyft's board.",
  "Rakuten spent $900 million in 2014 to buy messaging service Viber, which competes with Facebook's WhatsApp. "
